text.section:
In offering insurance and other forms of credit enhancement, the Department shall adopt eligibility standards that are reasonable to aid in:
financing the purchase, construction, or rehabilitation of:
housing projects;
special housing facility projects, consisting of the acquisition, rehabilitation, improvement, renovation, construction, financing, or refinancing of a building that:
rehabilitation projects, as defined in § 4-901 of this article;
energy conservation projects;
solar energy projects;
public purpose projects; or
infrastructure projects; and
the sale or other transfer of an obligation that is:
denoted as a bond, note, collateralized obligation, grantor trust, conduit, or other form of security or obligation; and
backed directly or indirectly by a mortgage or a payment derived from a mortgage.
